    public interface IBatchedFeatureExtractor<WINDATA,FDATA>

    Author:
    dawood

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      Iterable<? extends ILabeledFeatureGram<FDATA>[]> nextBatch(List<? extends ILabeledDataWindow<WINDATA>> data, FeatureExtractionPipeline<WINDATA,FDATA> fep)
      Get the next batch of extracted features from the given batch of data windows.

    • Method Detail

      • nextBatch

        Iterable<? extends ILabeledFeatureGram<FDATA>[]> nextBatch(List<? extends ILabeledDataWindow<WINDATA>> data,
                                                           FeatureExtractionPipeline<WINDATA,FDATA> fep)
        Get the next batch of extracted features from the given batch of data windows.
        Parameters:
        data - the labeled data from which labeled features are extracted.
        fep - the feature extraction function applied to the IDataWindow in a ILabeledDataWindow obtained from the data iterator.
        Returns:
        null if no more features could be extracted, otherwise a non-empty iterable over features extracted from the data windows with one feature for each data window. The returned iterable should iterate over the features in the same order as the given data windows if you want repeatable (accuracy) results.
